<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="387" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,341,582]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,341,366]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[394,584,341,366]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trebacosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marxi">
<emphasis box="[394,584,341,366]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Trebacosa marxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from those of T. 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1140,342,365]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trebacosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="europaea">
<emphasis box="[1036,1140,342,365]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">europaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the massive and wide median apophysis, 1.2 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[703,789,377,402]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 24" captionStartId="6.[151,264,994,1016]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,972]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,972]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 24. SEM images of Trebacosa male copulatory organs. 23 Trebacosa marxi (Stone, 1890), ventral view; 24 Trebacosa europaea Szinetár &amp; Kancsal, 2007, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242304/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
, see also Szinetár &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kancsal" box="[1040,1215,377,402]" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" refString="Szinetar, Cs. &amp; Kancsal, B. (2007 b) Trebacosa europaea, a new wolf spider from Hungary (Araneae, Lycosidae). Journal of Arachnology, 35, 153 - 158. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1636 / H 06 - 23.1" type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="b">Kancsal 2007b</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 6; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dondale" pageId="3" pageNumber="387" refString="Dondale, C. D. &amp; Redner, J. H. (1981) Classification of two North American species of Pirata, with a description of a new genus (Araneae, Lycosidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 170, 106 - 110." type="journal article" year="1981">Dondale &amp; Redner 1981</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2). Females can be distinguished by the large vulval chamber, which has a diameter about twice as large as the head of spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[561,630,449,474]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1748,1770]" captionTargetBox="[177,1430,195,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[177,1462,195,1735]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Female of Trebacosa marxi (Stone, 1890). 1 habitus, dorsal view; 2 epigyne, ventral view; 3 cleared epigyne, ventral view; 4 vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars are 1.0 mm for habitus, 0.25 mm for vulva images." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242300/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="387">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
